    <div class="stack mb-5">
      <h5> Internet of Things (IoT) </h5>
      <p>
        The internet of Things (IoT) refers to inter connection of everyday devices and objects through internet. The
        devices which is connected
        to the internet called as "smart device" and are equipped with sensors, software, and connectivity to collect or
        exchange data.
      </p>
      <p>

        The number of IoT devices is expected to grow rapidly
        in the next few years, with many devices from cars to
        refrigerators becomes "smart" or being connected to the internet.
      </p>

      <p>IoT is used in varius industires like:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Healthcare</li>
        <li>Manufacturing</li>
        <li>Smart Cities</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        Learning how to develop and manage these "smart" devices will be in high demand. <br>
        Prerequisites for learning IoT is basic understanding of Electronics, Networking Basics, Microcontrollers and
        Microprocessors and Programming languages like C/C++, Python, JavaScript, or others
        depending on the device and platform.
      </p>




    </div>

    <div class="stack mb-5">
      <h5>Data Science and Big Data</h5>
      <p>Data is everything it is now refered as the "new oil". We live in an era where data is generated at an
        unprecedented rate. As the amount of data generated per second increases, the ability to manage and use this
        data is in high demand.
      </p>
      <p>
        Data helps to analyze, optimize operations, make informed decisions, targeted adverts, risk assessment etc. The
        data is used to nearly every sector but most important sectors are:
      <ul>
        <li>Business Decisions</li>
        <li>Healthcare</li>
        <li>Finance</li>
        <li>Marketing</li>
      </ul>
      </p>


      <p>Learning to manage and play with data is very high in demand and will be so in future. To learn one should have
        good comand in basic mathematical concepts like statistics, probablity, Proficiency in programming languages
        like Python, R, or SQL is essential, knowledge of Hadoop is also useful.</p>

    </div>



    <div class="stack mb-5">
      <h5>Cyber Security</h5>
      <p>
        In this digitized world where the data is generated at unprecedented rate every second, the importance of
        cybersecurity cannot be overstated.
        As data breaches and cyber froude continue to make headlines, businesses and governments are paying more and
        more attention to cyber Security.
        Cyber Security helps in Protecting Sensitive Data, Preserving Privacy, National Security.
        It involves deploying people, policies, processes and technologies to protect organizations and their sensitive
        data from cyberthreats.
      </p>

      <p>
        CyberSecurity requires knowledge of computer systems, networks, knowledge of hardware, software, operating
        systems, and network protocols and at least one programming language (Java, C#, C++, PHP)
      </p>

    </div>




    <div class="stack mb-5">
      <h5>Blockchain</h5>
      <p>
        Blockchain technology is increasingly being used in industries such as healthcare and real estate, as well as
        financial applications such as banking and supply chains. Blockchain is a decentralized that enables secure and
        transparent transactions.
        <br>
        Some useful application of Blockchain are:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Smart Contracts</li>
        <li>Healthcare</li>
        <li>Identity Verification</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        Blockchain technology has the potential to revolutionize various industries by providing transparency, security,
        and trust in digital transactions.
        To learn blockchain, you should have familiarity with cryptographic concepts like hashing, public-private key
        pairs, and digital signatures, knowledge of networking and proficiency in programming languages, particularly languages used for blockchain development like Solidity (for Ethereum).
      </p>

    </div>






    <div class="stack mb-5">
      <h5>Cloud  Computing</h5>
      <p>
        Cloud computing is becoming popular and important as companies seek to reduce their IT costs and improve their flexibility to store, process, and manage  data.
        Cloud computing has become the backbone of modern businesses. Leading Cloud Service Providers are Amazon Web Services AWS, Microsoft Azure,Google Cloud Platform (GCP),IBM Cloud. Some key role of cloud computing are:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Scalability</li>
        <li>Cost-Efficiency</li>
        <li>Data Security</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        Learning how to develop and manage cloud-based solutions will be an important skill in the coming years. It is recommended to have proficiency in programming languages, particularly Python,
        concepts such as networks, servers, and storage, Operating Systems, knowledge of networking concepts, including IP addressing, routing, and firewalls, is essential for setting up and securing cloud environments.
      </p>
    </div>






    <div class="stack mb-5">
      <h5>Augmented Reality (AR) and Virtual Reality (VR)</h5>

      <p>AR and VR are already being used in multiple industires like gaming and healthcare. 
        AR is commonly experienced through smartphones, AR glasses, or heads-up displays mostly used by E-commerce platform. VR is typically experienced using headsets that blocks out the physical world mosty used in gaming.
        <br>
        AR and VR are at the forefront of technology, offering many possibilities for entertainment, education, and industry.
      </p>

      <p>

        To get started in AR/VR development, you'll need programming skills in languages ​​such as Java, C#, Swift, and Javascript. You will also need experience making 3D models and working with video game engines such as Unity or Unreal.
        The strong foundation in mathematical concepts like geometry, linear algebra.
      </p>
     

    </div>






    <div class="stack mb-5">
      <h5>UI/UX </h5>
<p>
  User Interface (UI) and User Experience (UX) design both play a critical role in the success of a product or service.
  UI design focuses on the actual construction of that product or service. UX design involves managing the user journey as they interact with a product or service.

</p>
<p>
  The field of UI/UX design is evolving rapidly as user expectations are changing or evolving rapidly. The key application of the UX/UI design are :
  Personalization, Accessibility, Ethical Design.

</p>
<p>
  To get a job in as a UI/UX designer one should have familiarity with design tools like Adobe XD, Sketch, or Figma,  the basics of HTML and CSS can be beneficial. UI/UX design requires creativity and ability to think out of the box.
</p>
<p>
  Learn the basics, Build a portfolio, get feedback and practice, design is the game of practice the more time you give more better you became.
</p>

    </div>


    
    <div class="stack mb-5">
      <h5>Quantum Computing </h5>
      <p>
        Quantum Computing has a potential to revolutionize computing as we know it. Unlike classical bits, which can represent either a 0 or a 1, quantum bits or qubits can exist in multiple states simultaneously that allows quantum computers to tackle complex problems.
        Quantum Computing is still in early stages. The leading companies in this field are IBM, Google, and startups like Rigetti.
      </p>
      <p>
        Quantum computers currently are primarily used for research, optimization problems, and cryptography and have promising future in various industires for Optimization, Materials Science, AI and Machine Learning.

      </p>
      <p>
        Quantum computing is a highly specialized field, beginners should have strong foundation in mathematical concepts like Linear Algebra, Probability and Statistics, basics of quantum mechanics Proficiency in programming languages like Python is essential for writing quantum algorithms.
        Quantum development environments like Qiskit (IBM), Cirq (Google), or Quantum Development Kit (Microsoft)
      </p>
    </div>





    <div class="stack mb-5">
      <h5>DevOps </h5>
      <p>
        DevOps can be referd as a set of practices for software development that aim to bridge the gap between development (Dev) and operations (Ops). DevOps emphasizes collaboration, automation, and efficiency.
        Demand for DevOps professionals will continue to grow as companies seek to streamline their software development processes.
      </p>
      <p>
        Some useful applications of DevOps are:
<ul>
  <li>DevSecOps : Integrating security (Sec) into DevOps practices</li>
  <li>Serverless Computing</li>
  <li>Microservices and Containers</li>
</ul>
      </p>
      <p>
        To start a career in DevOps, you should know basic understanding of software development, scripting languages like Bash, Python, or PowerShell, Learn version control systems like Git, Understanding Linux commands, Containerization. DevOps relies on effective teamwork and communication so develop collaboration and communication.
      </p>
      </div>

